## 10. Theming Changes

### Theme Props Removed (theming no longer handled React-side)
| Component | Removed Prop | Replacement |
|-----------|-------------|-------------|
| Avatar | `border` | `isBordered` |
| Masthead | `backgroundColor` | Use CSS theming / dark mode |
| Nav | `theme` | Use light/dark mode theming |
| PageSidebar | `theme` | Use light/dark mode theming |
| PageSection | `variant` (most values) | Only `"default"` or `"secondary"` |

### Color Variant Changes
| Component | Old Value | New Value |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| Drawer* | `colorVariant="light-200"` | `colorVariant="secondary"` |
| DrawerContent | `colorVariant="no-background"` | Removed |
| Tabs | `variant="light300"` | `variant="secondary"` |
| Banner/Label | `color="cyan"` | `color="teal"` |
| Banner/Label | `color="gold"` | `color="yellow"` |

### Dark Theme
- PF6 introduces built-in dark theme support via design tokens
- No longer use `theme` props on components
- CSS custom properties automatically adjust for dark mode
- Use `--pf-t--*` token system which supports both light and dark themes

