## 11. Breakpoint Changes

PF6 uses **rem units** instead of pixels for breakpoints:

| Breakpoint | Token | Old (px) | New (rem) |
|------------|-------|----------|-----------|
| xs | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xs` | 0px | 0rem |
| sm | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--sm` | 576px | 36rem |
| md | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--md` | 768px | 48rem |
| lg | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--lg` | 992px | 62rem |
| xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--xl` | 1200px | 75rem |
| 2xl | `--pf-t--global--breakpoint--2xl` | 1450px | 90.625rem |

**Action**: Update any custom JS/TS logic that uses hardcoded pixel values for breakpoints. Divide px by 16 to get rem equivalent.

**Codemod**: вқҢ No вҖ” manual

---

## 12. Test Failures to Expect

### Button Tests
1. **`aria-disabled` not found**: PF6 Button uses `disabled` attribute instead of `aria-disabled`. Remove tests checking for `aria-disabled="false"` or matching `aria-disabled` to `isDisabled` when `component="button"`.
2. **`byText` returns wrong element**: Button text is now wrapped in `<span>`. Use `screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'Button text' })` instead of `screen.getByText('Button text')`.

### Select Tests
1. **`byRole` can't find menu options**: After selection, Popper menu may have `aria-disabled`. Pass `{ hidden: true }` option or set `appendTo="inline"`.

### General Test Updates
- **Snapshot tests**: Will break due to markup changes, CSS class renames (`pf-v5` вҶ’ `pf-v6`), and structural changes
- **TreeView**: `pf-m-selectable` class removed from list items
- **Pagination**: New wrapper element around PaginationOptionsMenu toggle
- **AccordionItem**: Now renders `div` wrapper
- **NotificationBadge**: Uses stateful button internally
- **NotificationDrawerHeader**: Uses `h1` instead of Text component
- **LoginMainHeader**: Uses `div` instead of `header` element
- **WizardFooter**: Uses ActionList around Buttons
- **WizardNavItem**: New `pf-v6-c-wizard__nav-link-main` wrapper

---

## 13. What Codemods Handle vs Manual Work

### вң… Handled by Codemods (with `--fix`)
- Prop renames (e.g., `isActive` вҶ’ `isClicked`, `labelIcon` вҶ’ `labelHelp`)
- Prop removals (e.g., `theme`, `backgroundColor`, `hasNoPadding`)
- Component renames (e.g., `Text` вҶ’ `Content`, `MastheadBrand` вҶ’ `MastheadLogo`)
- Import path moves (deprecated вҶ’ `/deprecated`, next вҶ’ core, charts вҶ’ `/victory`)
- Chip вҶ’ Label replacement
- EmptyState restructuring (partial)
- Toolbar chip вҶ’ label prop renames
- Toolbar spacer вҶ’ gap conversion
- Toolbar variant renames
- Color value updates (cyan вҶ’ teal, gold вҶ’ yellow)
- Token prefix updates (`global_*` вҶ’ `t_global_*`)
- CSS variable renames for non-color global tokens
- Class name prefix updates (`pf-v5` вҶ’ `pf-v6`)
- KebabToggle вҶ’ MenuToggle replacement
- LoginMainFooterLinksItem restructuring
- Masthead structure updates
- Various enum/interface renames

### вҡ пёҸ Partially Handled (codemod fixes some, manual review needed)
- EmptyState refactoring (complex compositions may need manual adjustment)
- Banner `variant` вҶ’ `color`/`status` (may need `status` instead of `color`)
- Button icon migration (only `variant="plain"` auto-fixed)
- Global color token replacement (set to hot pink placeholder вҖ” **must manually choose correct token**)

### вқҢ Requires Manual Work
- Removed deprecated components (Application Launcher, Context Selector, old Dropdown, Options Menu, Page Header, old Select)
- Component/chart-level CSS token replacements
- Breakpoint pixel вҶ’ rem logic updates
- Custom CSS override removal/updating
- DrawerPanelBody separation from DrawerHead
- NavItem icon prop migration
- MenuToggle icon-only toggle pattern
- Test updates (snapshots, queries, `aria-disabled` checks)
- `href` required on JumpLinksItem
- SimpleFileUpload `browseButtonAriaDescribedby` prop
- LogViewer stylesheet import update
- FeedbackModal CSS import update
- `appendTo` default change awareness (Dropdown, Select, Popper вҶ’ `document.body`)
- TreeView `pf-m-selectable` class removal in tests
- Products using custom CSS to replicate PatternFly styling (full re-skin needed)

---

## Quick Reference: Codemod Commands

```bash
# 1. Main codemods
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest ./src --v6 --fix

# 2. Class name updater
npx @patternfly/class-name-updater ./src --v6 --fix

# 3. CSS vars updater (for .css/.scss files)
npx @patternfly/css-vars-updater ./src

# 4. Final cleanup
npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest ./src --v6 --only data-codemods-cleanup --fix
```

