        <tr><td>Specific instances</td>
          <td>ChatMessageMarkdown.tsx, NamespacesPage.tsx</td>
          <td>AboutUIModal, FileAttachment, DebugInformation, HelpDropdown, TLSInfo, ManualRefreshEmptyState, RefreshButton, NamespaceActions (MenuToggle), and more</td>
        </tr>
        <tr><td>MenuToggle icon migration</td><td style="color:var(--red);">No</td><td style="color:var(--green);">Yes (multiple files)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Correct implementation</td><td style="color:var(--green);">Yes</td><td style="color:var(--green);">Yes</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Both branches apply the icon prop pattern correctly. Goose covers substantially more instances, including the related <code>MenuToggle</code> icon migration pattern (<code>&lt;MenuToggle&gt;&lt;Icon/&gt;&lt;/MenuToggle&gt;</code> вҶ’ <code>&lt;MenuToggle icon={&lt;Icon/&gt;} /&gt;</code>).</p>
