</details>

<!-- 6.5 Navigation -->
<details id="detail-nav">
  <summary>
    <span>рҹ§ӯ Navigation &amp; Masthead</span>
    <span class="winner-tag">Winner: Goose</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="detail-content">
    <h4>pf-codemods-053126-1704: рҹҡЁ BROKEN Navigation.tsx</h4>
    <p>The codemods branch introduced a <strong>critically broken</strong> MastheadBrand/MastheadLogo nesting:</p>
    <pre><code class="diff-del">// PRODUCED BY CODEMODS (BROKEN):
&lt;MastheadBrand data-codemods&gt;&lt;MastheadLogo data-codemods&gt;
  &lt;MastheadBrand data-codemods&gt;&lt;MastheadLogo component={linkProps =&gt; &lt;Link {...linkProps} to="/" /&gt;}&gt;
    &lt;img src={...} alt="Kiali Logo" /&gt;
  &lt;/MastheadLogo&gt;&lt;/MastheadBrand&gt;
&lt;/MastheadLogo&gt;&lt;/MastheadBrand&gt;</code></pre>
    <p>Issues:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Double nesting:</strong> MastheadBrand вҶ’ MastheadLogo вҶ’ MastheadBrand вҶ’ MastheadLogo. The outer pair is meaningless.</li>
      <li><strong>4x <code>data-codemods</code> attributes</strong> вҖ” codemod scaffolding that should have been removed with <code>--only data-codemods-cleanup</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Will render incorrect DOM:</strong> Two nested MastheadBrand elements produce invalid PatternFly layout structure.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The <code>main</code> branch already had the correct PF6 structure. This codemod output is a <strong>net regression</strong>.</p>

    <h4>semver/goose/053126-1509: Correct changes</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><code>Navigation.tsx</code>: <code>isHamburgerButton</code> вҶ’ <code>hamburgerVariant="collapse"</code> (correct PF6 API change for PageToggleButton)</li>
      <li><code>Menu.tsx</code>: <code>Divider</code> вҶ’ <code>NavItemSeparator</code> inside Nav context (correct PF6 pattern)</li>
      <li>MastheadBrand/MastheadLogo structure preserved correctly (no regression)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

