<div class="card">
  <h4>вҡ пёҸ Known Bug in semver/goose: ValidationStack.tsx</h4>
  <p>The <code>StackItem</code> <code>component</code> prop expects a <code>React.ElementType</code> (like <code>'div'</code>, <code>'span'</code>, or a component class) вҖ” it's used internally as <code>&lt;Component ...&gt;</code>.
     The Goose branch incorrectly passes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>A JSX element (<code>&lt;Validation .../&gt;</code>) as <code>component</code> вҖ” this will fail at runtime because React can't instantiate an already-rendered element</li>
    <li>A string (<code>"Istio validations"</code>) as <code>component</code> вҖ” this creates an HTML element named <code>&lt;Istio validations&gt;</code> which is invalid HTML</li>
  </ul>
  <pre><code>// BUG вҖ” component receives a React element instance, not a component type
&lt;StackItem component={&lt;Validation severity={check.severity} message="..." /&gt;} /&gt;

// FIX вҖ” use children (the original pattern was correct)
&lt;StackItem&gt;&lt;Validation severity={check.severity} message="..." /&gt;&lt;/StackItem&gt;</code></pre>
  <p><strong>Impact:</strong> Medium вҖ” affects tooltip validation displays. Fix is trivial: revert to the original children-based pattern.</p>
</div>

